Betfred Offers Industry Two Seats on Tote Board, Telegraph Says

-- B y   M i c h e l l e   E .   F r a z e r
-- 
2011-05-22T08:20:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-22/betfred-offers-industry-two-seats-on-tote-board-telegraph-says.html
Betfred Ltd. plans to create an
advisory board with two seats for racecourse industry
representatives if it’s successful in its bid for U.K.
government-owned bookmaker  the Tote , the Telegraph reported,
without saying where it got the information.  The “Tote Development Board” would serve to align the
interests of the bookmaker and the racing industry, according to
the newspaper. Rival bidder Sports Investment Partners has also
promised two board seats to industry representatives, the
Telegraph said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Michelle E. Frazer in London at 
 mfrazer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  